&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Senior Team Leader Band 7 Cardiothoracic Theatres &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; University Hospital Plymouth NHS Trust has an exciting opportunity for Senior Team Leader Band 7 role in the Cardiothoracic Theatre Unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; We are seeking to appoint a highly motivated individual with experience in Cardiothoracic surgery and can demonstrate the ability to provide excellent clinical leadership and management skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant  will be joining an innovative multi-discipline team that is on the forefront of leading innovation within this exciting surgical speciality. The expectation of this role will be to deliver safe, efficient quality care in line with the Trust core values and be proactive in the on going programme for improvement, which allows us to constantly review our practice and perioperative pathways.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Plymouth Hospitals is a large acute NHS trust in the Southwest of England, situated on the Devon and Cornwall border and provides perioperative care for elective and emergency patients across the region.  The hospital is a designated Trauma Centre and tertiary referral centre for Cardiac patients.  The trust is a teaching hospital with close links to the Peninsula Medical School and the University of Plymouth.  Staff locating to this region will be able enjoy the benefits of a cosmopolitan city and outstanding areas of natural beauty such as Dartmoor National Park and the wonderful beaches of Devon and Cornwall.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you require any additional information please contact Matron Michelle Smith.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; michelle-jane.smith@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
